</div>
</body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Ossuary has inner ledge on three sides, traces of red wash, low feet, and flat, sliding lid. Ornamentation, on the chest's front side, consists of a "running-dog" frame within a metope frame, containing a degenerated two-columned porch motif flanked on left and right by six-petalled rosettes within concentric line circles. The name is a contraction of Ἐζεκίας attested on other ossuaries and in the Septuagint and Josephus. Ἐζεκίας derives from חזקיה, itself a common contraction of יחזקיהו. The ossuary contained tiny bronze nails in addition to bones, probably belt-studs.</p>
         </div>
